{"key":"processedPost-11854944","value":{"id":11854944,"first":11854450,"last":11855610,"when":1263863325,"utime":"01/19/10 03:08 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>screekrunner said:</strong><br />Do you guys boil it for an hour? </blockquote><br />No, much longer.&nbsp; Your jars should be elevated <i>above</i> the water, not in it.&nbsp; It isn't about when the water boils, but when the steam begins to surround the jars after the thermal inertia of the cold jars has been overcome.<br />Use a pot with a tight fitting lid, and don't begin counting the time until steam is escaping from under the lid.&nbsp; At this point, turn down the stove to the minimum setting that will keep steam escaping, but just barely.&nbsp; Time for <b>90 minutes</b> after that point.&nbsp; Add water if necessary during the cycle to keep the pot from boiling dry.&nbsp; It's OK to open the lid to look in and see how much water is left.&nbsp; If you see you're going to need more water, it's a good idea to boil it in another small pan first and then pour it in, thus you don't cool off your sterilization pot.<br />You can see a video of the whole process on my <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">website</a>.<br />RR","title":"Re: boiling method of sterilizing jars?"}}